1
00:00:00,459 --> 00:00:02,461
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,503 --> 00:00:03,754
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:07,132
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,511
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:11,553
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,680
Adventure Time

7
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:15,182
Come on, grab your friends

8
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,851
We'll go to very distant lands

9
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:20,145
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

10
00:00:20,229 --> 00:00:21,897
The fun will never end

11
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:24,107
It's Adventure Time

12
00:00:32,199 --> 00:00:33,909
(HUMMING)

13
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:37,162
BEEMO: One free-range Humpty Dumpty.

14
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:39,957
Sorry.

15
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:45,212
Fine aged Cheddar man.

16
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:52,928
Homemade ketchup.

17
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:53,971
(GAGS)

18
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:55,055
(SWISHING)

19
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:57,975
(GROANING)

20
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:02,229
A fresh pepper fart.

21
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:03,438
(FARTING)

22
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:05,399
Dance, parsley.

23
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:09,319
(SQUISH)

24
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:10,821
Face bread.

25
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:13,907
Special sentient sandwich.

26
00:01:15,284 --> 00:01:18,036
(CLICK, WHIRRING)

27
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:19,705
(WHOOSHING)

28
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:21,164
(CLICK, WHIRRING AND WHOOSHING STOP)

29
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:24,918
Mmm... Is that special sentient sammich?

30
00:01:25,168 --> 00:01:26,545
Bingo!

31
00:01:26,587 --> 00:01:28,422
Made by the Beemo.

32
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:31,216
Beemo, you're my little cherub.
You know that?

33
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:33,051
You made all this for me, right?

34
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:34,344
Aaahhh.

35
00:01:34,678 --> 00:01:35,929
Not so fast, Jake.

36
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:37,723
No. (GROANS)

37
00:01:37,973 --> 00:01:41,101
The sammiches are yours...
For a price.

38
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:42,227
What?

39
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:44,855
I need you to be my tiny horse for the day,

40
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:48,358
so I can do my live-action
cowboy role-play adventure.

41
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:51,111
No way. Poo deal.

42
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:52,863
I'll do 20 minutes.

43
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:56,617
It took me over six hours
to prepare this nosh, Jake.

44
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:59,703
Not to mention the time it took
acquiring the ingredients

45
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:01,204
through the "special market,"

46
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:03,874
putting my safety
and my reputation on the line.

47
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:06,084
Okay, fine, fine.

48
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,879
Three sammiches for every hour I'm a horse.

49
00:02:09,004 --> 00:02:10,047
Mmm...

50
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:13,550
One sammich per horse-hour,
six-hour minimum.

51
00:02:13,884 --> 00:02:15,052
Deal.

52
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,513
Yippee-ki-yay!

53
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,308
Om! Mmm.

54
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,060
(MUNCHING, GULPS)

55
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:24,311
Oh, yeah.

56
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:26,021
It tastes alive.

57
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:27,814
(MUNCHING)

58
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:29,149
(THUD AND SPURS JANGLE)

59
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:33,070
Steed yourself, partner.

60
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:34,821
Okay.

61
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,573
Hmm. (GULPS)

62
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:42,537
(CREAKING)

63
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:43,580
'Kay.

64
00:02:43,789 --> 00:02:45,582
Oh, come on, man.

65
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,167
You didn't even try.

66
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,461
I did try. Horses are hard.

67
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:50,545
(CREAKS)

68
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:51,713
(STRAINS)

69
00:02:51,922 --> 00:02:52,923
(GROANS)

70
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,049
How's that?

71
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:56,218
Eh, it reads.

72
00:02:56,468 --> 00:02:58,720
(SPURS JINGLING)

73
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:06,978
Steady, girl.

74
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:08,605
- What...
- (SHUSHING)

75
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,607
I'm going to mount you now.

76
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,317
Hup!

77
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,861
- Good girl.
- (GROANS)

78
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:16,488
So, what's the plan anyway, Beemo?

79
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:20,492
The plan is to punch the toads to the stump

80
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:23,495
and bring justice to the peeps!

81
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:24,621
Oow!

82
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,373
Oh, and by the way, Jake,

83
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:29,501
from now on, you can call me..."Angel Face".

84
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:31,837
- Hyah!
- Youch!

85
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:39,761
I used to be a guy who ran from glob

86
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:43,515
with the wind at my back
and the devil on my shoulder.

87
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,726
Now I'm the guy chasing those guys,

88
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:49,980
yet the devil is still here,
sleeping in my couch.

89
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:52,899
Beemo, that hurt when you dug your boots
into my side belly.

90
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:54,526
Are you gonna apologize or...

91
00:03:54,609 --> 00:03:56,027
Horses do not talk.

92
00:03:56,153 --> 00:03:57,154
Over there! Hyah!

93
00:03:57,279 --> 00:03:58,280
- (SPUR PLUNGES)
- (GROANS)

94
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:02,159
Whoa!

95
00:04:03,535 --> 00:04:05,287
Jackrabbit Johnson.

96
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:06,496
(SPITS)

97
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:08,915
This guy's wanted for stealing piglets

98
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:11,418
from their mothers while they are feeding.

99
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:12,753
Makes me sick.

100
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:15,172
(CHEWING)

101
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:21,136
He was last seen in Dead Goat Gulch.

102
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,512
What do you say, girl?

103
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:24,848
Want to catch this donkey
and split the reward?

104
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:25,891
(SMACKS)

105
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:29,269
You have 45 minutes left
before my next sammich.

106
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:30,771
Time's a-wasting!

107
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:32,022
- (SPURS PLUNGE)
- Yee!

108
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,523
(LAUGHS)

109
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:41,907
Hmm.

110
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,618
(PANTING)

111
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:46,286
(GROANS) Beemo, I'm tired.

112
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,997
Looks like my horse needs a rest.

113
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:50,791
Slow down, horse.

114
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:51,917
(SIGHS)

115
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,669
(HUMMING)

116
00:05:01,635 --> 00:05:05,388
(SINGING) Being a robot cowboy

117
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:08,183
Is a lonely job

118
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:16,566
But somebody has to protect the piglets

119
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:18,902
(ALL GASP)

120
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:23,782
I got nobody but my horse

121
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:27,828
And my friend the Cactus Guy

122
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:32,541
It's okay because I like them a lot

123
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:37,045
That's okay,
I like being a robot cowboy

124
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:40,298
(HUMMING)

125
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:41,591
- (CHOMPING)
- (HUMMING)

126
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:44,177
(HUMMING)

127
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:52,602
BEEMO: Be careful, Jake.

128
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,563
This is where Jackrabbit Johnson's

129
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:57,607
gang of lowlife bandits lays low.

130
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,119
(GASPS) Hyah!

131
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,497
Bang! Bang!
Put them up, partner!

132
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:13,832
Hyah!

133
00:06:14,124 --> 00:06:15,500
Pew, pew.
Pew, pew, pew!

134
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,131
I want answers!

135
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:23,633
(AS SOCKS) "You can't do this to us."

136
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:26,595
No answers, eh? No use to me!

137
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:29,848
How about you, Frisco?

138
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,892
(AS FRISCO) "I'm not going to talk."

139
00:06:31,975 --> 00:06:33,351
Why am I talking to you then?

140
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:34,394
(GRUNTING)

141
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,521
(GRUNTING)

142
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:39,900
(CHEWING, CHUCKLES)

143
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,276
(YELPS, GROANS)

144
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,865
Beemo, what did you do?

145
00:06:47,032 --> 00:06:50,911
It's Jackrabbit Johnson's
right-hand man, Tumbleweed Turk.

146
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:54,372
I spent the last three months
building all of this.

147
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:55,790
Oh, that's where you been?

148
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:57,000
Mmm-hmm.

149
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:59,127
Beemo gave me a Finn cake.

150
00:07:01,046 --> 00:07:02,923
Don't talk to my horse, Tumbleweed.

151
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:04,925
- (BEEMO GRUNTS)
- (TUMBLEWEED GROANS)

152
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,801
Where is Jackrabbit Johnson?

153
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:08,929
I know you know where he's headed.

154
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:10,555
I don't know.

155
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,308
Tumbleweed Turk's always the last to know.

156
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:16,895
It's just like I told the other
bounty hunter, I swear.

157
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:19,439
I don't believe a word you say.

158
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:23,068
Now, take a message to your compadre.

159
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:27,280
Tell him his old pal Angel Face
is itching to get together.

160
00:07:27,322 --> 00:07:31,576
Tell Jackrabbit Johnson
to meet me at Dirtwater Flats,

161
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:33,328
just like the old days!

162
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:35,455
IS

163
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,456
Okay.

164
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,083
(WHIRRING)

165
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,836
Sock citizens of Dead Goat Gulch,

166
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,171
we can rebuild!

167
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:44,965
(WHISTLES)

168
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:47,926
(NEIGHS)

169
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:52,347
- (SPURS JANGLE)
- (GROANS)

170
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:57,727
(WIND WHOOSHING)

171
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,482
(SNARLS)

172
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,444
(GALLOPING)

173
00:08:11,491 --> 00:08:12,742
Uh...

174
00:08:12,826 --> 00:08:15,620
I don't remember where Dirtwater Flat is.

175
00:08:16,121 --> 00:08:17,497
Better stop for the night.

176
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,749
We can make a campfire here.

177
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,001
And we will talk about

178
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:23,128
what we will do with the reward money.

179
00:08:23,253 --> 00:08:24,254
No.

180
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:27,340
It's been fun, Beemo,
but it's time to go home

181
00:08:27,382 --> 00:08:29,718
because there are no more sandwiches.

182
00:08:32,387 --> 00:08:34,681
But I want to finish the adventure.

183
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:38,309
Which direction is the house?

184
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:43,064
I'm not sure.

185
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,444
(GASPS) Get down!

186
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:52,949
Getting kicked out of the Guild of Assassins...
Check.

187
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:56,036
Capturing my first bounty...
Check. (MUNCHING)

188
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,455
Going to Finn and Jake's treehouse
and getting revenge...

189
00:08:58,538 --> 00:08:59,789
Unchecked.

190
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:01,082
JACKRABBIT JOHNSON: Finn and
Jake's treehouse?

191
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:02,167
Mmm-hmm.

192
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,836
Who are you,
and why do you want to get revenge?

193
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:07,422
I am Me-Mow!

194
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:09,549
Me-Mow? Whoa.

195
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:10,717
You've gotten bigger.

196
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,552
Have we met before?

197
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,220
JAKE: Finn, is that you?

198
00:09:14,429 --> 00:09:16,347
That's Jackrabbit Johnson!

199
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:17,474
Finn?

200
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:19,684
It is Finn!

201
00:09:19,851 --> 00:09:21,227
Tricked again!

202
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:23,229
Look, it's Me-Mow, Beemo.

203
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,231
I don't care. That's my bounty!

204
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:26,691
- (EXCLAIMS)
- (GROANS)

205
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,110
Jake, transform... Horse!

206
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,204
Whoa! Did you have a real gun all this time?

207
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,872
I am old enough to vote.

208
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:45,877
ME-MOW: (THINKING) Hey, Jake, if you
can hear my internal monologue,

209
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:47,754
I'm going to Kill you.

210
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,006
(CHUCKLES EVILLY)

211
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:51,382
(BLOWS)

212
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:52,717
(RATTLING)

213
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:54,135
(RATTLESNAKE GROANS)

214
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,638
(WHIZZING)

215
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:03,019
Your daisy days are over!

216
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,523
I am the whaler 'round these parts!

217
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:13,530
Huh.

218
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:17,784
(SIZZLING)

219
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:22,163
(GUN CLICKS)

220
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,666
Sounds like you're out of ammo.

221
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,668
No, you heard incorrectly.

222
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:27,919
Bang, bang, bang!

223
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:29,671
(LAUGHS)

224
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,131
I'm coming for you.

225
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,423
(WHIZZING)

226
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:34,926
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

227
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,511
(GRUNTS)

228
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:37,887
(BLOWS)

229
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:43,184
Blast you, Finn and Jake and Angel Face.

230
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,062
This prison cell's not going to hold me.

231
00:10:46,271 --> 00:10:47,647
Oh?

232
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:54,696
Hey, Finn and Jake! I'll get my revenge!

233
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,030
You hear me?

234
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:57,323
ME-MOW: Revenge!

235
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:00,160
Hey, Beemo, are you sure you took down
all the wanted posters?

236
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,286
Yes.

237
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:04,330
- Stick 'em up.
- Huh?

238
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:07,458
This bounty belongs to me.

239
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:08,585
Get out of here!

240
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:09,794
(SCREAMS)

241
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:10,962
Thanks, Beemo.

242
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:12,422
(IN TOUGH VOICE) You're welcome.

243
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:18,803
Come along with me

244
00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:23,099
And the butterflies and bees

245
00:11:26,311 --> 00:11:28,188
This party is so crazy!

